SUMMARY:The Complicated Impact of the 1619 Project on African American History
DESCRIPTION:This is a free Adult School presentation.\n\nMontclair State 
 University Associate Dean Dr. Leslie Wilson will lead a panel of scholars 
 in a discussion on the creation and controversy surrounding the New York 
 Times' interpretative multimedia initiative on American Slavery and its 
 complicated legacy on the future of African American history instruction in 
 schools.\n\nMade possible by funds from the New Jersey State Council on the 
 Arts\, a partner agency of the National Endowment for the Arts.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Lectures / History & Culture
UID:LibCal-10306-16005090
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16005090
END:VEVENT
