SUMMARY:Everything Book Club\, "H is for Hawk" by Helen Macdonald
DESCRIPTION:This program was moved from Tuesday\, February 10\, to 
 Tuesday\, February 13. We hope you can still make it!\n\nSlated for release 
 as a major motion picture on January 26. An instant New York Times 
 bestseller and award-winning sensation. Recently bereaved\, the author 
 decides to adopt and raise one of nature's most vicious predators\, a 
 goshawk. She names her Mabel. By a writer\, poet\, and naturalist who works 
 at the Department of History and Philosophy of Science at the University of 
 Cambridge.\n\nPlease note: The Montclair Film Matinee Club will be meeting 
 on February 4\, at 2:30 p.m.\, at 505 Bloomfield Avenue to discuss the film 
 adaptation of “H is for Hawk.” They charge a fee of $15 to participate. 
 There will not be a screening of the film included in their 
 session.\n\n“Macdonald's book is so good that at times it hurt me to read 
 it.” —The New York Times\n\nHelen Macdonald is a writer\, poet\, and 
 naturalist. Before becoming a full-time writer\, they worked in raptor 
 research and conservation for many years\, then became a historian of 
 science\, specialising in the history of natural history\, ornithology\, 
 and animal behaviour. They are an Affiliated Research Scholar at the 
 Department of History and Philosophy of Science at the University of 
 Cambridge.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Tower Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Book Discussion
UID:LibCal-10306-15930112
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15930112
END:VEVENT
