BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260205T233000Z
DTEND:20260206T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260205T000000Z
SUMMARY:Erased Histories: Queer Cinema Before the Great Turn
DESCRIPTION:Contrary to popular belief\, LGBTQ  themes\, content\, 
 characters\, and situations have existed in cinema since the very dawn of 
 early silent film history. What's more\, Queer characters and content were 
 treated as safe\, acceptable\, and even enjoyable by contemporary audiences 
 and filmmakers alike. In this presentation\, Cinema Studies Professor 
 Cordelia Siporin will trace the historical trajectory of Queer Cinema from 
 its inception in the Queer-accepting silent and early sound eras through 
 the Great Turn--revealing how America retroactively shifted from an 
 egalitarian Queer-accepting space into the Queerphobic society it has since 
 become\, and how knowing this history can help us reclaim the truth of our 
 lost cultural past.
LOCATION:Montclair Bellevue Ave Branch - First Floor\, Montclair Bellevue Avenue Branch
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Bellevue Avenue Branch":MAILTO:branch-events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Bellevue Avenue Branch, Books, Film & Theater, Talk, Lecture
UID:LibCal-10306-16260659
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16260659
