SUMMARY:Friends of the Howe House presents: MLK 2026
DESCRIPTION:Two community-powered art installations reflecting on freedom\, 
 justice\, and democracy are coming to Montclair Public Library.\n\nAs our 
 nation approaches the 250th anniversary of the signing of the Declaration 
 of Independence\, we will come together to reflect on the promises made in 
 our founding documents and celebrate the ongoing work by people past and 
 present to fulfill them. This project is proudly funded by a grant from the 
 New Jersey MLK Jr. Commission. Join us for an immersive art installation 
 event featuring remarks from Artists\, Sound Bath Vocalists\, Community 
 Leaders\, and Howe House Board Members\, and more.\n\n
