SUMMARY:Urban Stomp Live: Defiant Joy\, Improvisation & Social Dances at MPL NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a free Adult School event. Click here to 
 register.\n\nPresented in partnership with the Institute of Jazz Studies at 
 Rutgers University-Newark and The Peter Bodge & Seed Artists Jazz Library 
 at MPL.\n\n\n\nJoin cultural anthropologist and curator Dr. Derrick León 
 Washington for an evening that moves through history\, rhythm\, and 
 community.\n\nDr. Washington—curator of Urban Stomp: Dreams & Defiance on 
 the Dance Floor\, currently on view at the Museum of the City of New 
 York—brings to life the story of social dance: from ragtime and the 
 Charleston to Lindy Hop\, Mambo\, and beyond. Through vivid storytelling\, 
 photographs\, rare video excerpts\, and the music that shaped each era\, 
 participants will experience how these dances carried both joy and 
 defiance.\n\nAfter the talk and Q&A\, stay for free food and a social dance 
 session—a chance to learn dance steps\, connect with neighbors\, and 
 dance together.\n\nMade possible by funds from the New Jersey State Council 
 on the Arts\, a partner agency of the National Endowment for the Arts.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Lectures / History & Culture, Music
UID:LibCal-10306-15631137
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15631137
