SUMMARY:Create Your Own Galentine's Day Floral Design NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to register. 
 Registration closes on Feb. 1.\n\n"What's Galentine's Day? Oh\, it's only 
 the best day of the year. Every February 13th\, my lady friends and I leave 
 our husbands and our boyfriends at home\, and we just come and kick it." 
 Amy Poehler\, Parks and Recreation. Or you could come to our Galentine's 
 Day class a couple of days beforehand and learn to make a sleek linear 
 floral design instead!\n\nFran Ackerly\, president of the Montclair Garden 
 Club\, will be taking us step by step through the creation of a modern 
 floral centerpiece design to give to your best friend or brighten up your 
 own home this February. Flowers\, containers and frogs are included. Bring 
 your own sharp scissors or yard clippers and your Galentine's Day cheer!
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Cafe Area\, Montclair Public Library
