SUMMARY:Bus Trip: Culinary Institute of America and Vanderbilt Mansion
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nNo refunds. Registration closes January 26. Go behind the 
 scenes of the CIA and get an inside look into their world of food with a 
 student-led tour and Q&A session. Enjoy a delicious three-course meal at 
 CIA's American Bounty Restaurant that serves contemporary and traditional 
 regional dishes with a focus on the seasons and products of the Hudson 
 Valley.\n\nThen we'll get back on the bus to the Vanderbilt Mansion 
 National Historic Site in nearby Hyde Park.  We'll visit the Visitor's 
 Center to find out more about this Gilded Age setting. Completed in 1899\, 
 the Vanderbilt Mansion is a gorgeous example of Beaux Arts architecture and 
 furnished lavishly in an array of historical styles\, with sweeping views 
 of the Hudson River. Finally\, we’ll return to Montclair at 6 p.m.
LOCATION:Montclair - Offsite\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
