SUMMARY:From Africa to America: The Poetry of Phillis Wheatley NEW - Virtual Program
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nIn 1761\, Phillis Wheatley arrived in Boston as an enslaved 
 girl from West Africa. As noted in her poem\, “On Being Brought from 
 Africa to America\,” Wheatley was well aware of that she and other 
 Africans were presumed inferior to whites\, yet she defied assumptions by 
 beguiling the literary world with her talent while implicitly challenging 
 the logic of her enslavement. In this course\, we examine Wheatley’s 
 poetry and her extraordinary life in the historical context of the American 
 Revolution and the burgeoning abolitionist movement of the late eighteenth 
 century.
LOCATION:Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Books, Film & Theater, Lectures / History & Culture
UID:LibCal-10306-15843396
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15843396
