SUMMARY:The American Renaissance: Thoreau\, Melville\, Douglass\, Whitman and Dickinson NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to register on 
 the Adult School website\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n			Henry David Thoreau. Herman 
 Melville. Frederick Douglass. Walt Whitman. Emily Dickinson. What did these 
 giants of American literature think about slavery and anti-slavery? Or 
 about capitalism? Or the emerging movement for women’s rights? What do 
 they have to say to us?”\n			\n		\n	\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Lectures / History & Culture
