SUMMARY:Advanced English to Speakers of Other Languages (ESOL) for Professionals
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nAdvanced ESL is for Individuals who want to build confidence 
 in their English proficiency skills and communicate with clarity\, 
 directness\, and the cultural sensitivity expected in a professional 
 organization setting. The course includes vocabulary-building activities 
 with a focus on higher level-appropriate\, key academic\, and 
 high-frequency vocabulary\, as well as listening\, speaking  and writing 
 exercises to build confidence and competence among the American English 
 speaking community. Prerequisite: Intermediate English fluency is 
 required\, this is not a beginner's class.\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Conference Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
UID:LibCal-10306-15816360
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15816360
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260217T231500Z
DTEND:20260218T004500Z
DTSTAMP:20260217T000000Z
SUMMARY:Practical Spanish 3: Basic Conversation
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nThis class is for those of you who are able to communicate in 
 Spanish at a novice level\, but want to continue to improve your 
 pronunciation and your knowledge of the language while increasing your 
 vocabulary. Presentations\, conversations and dialogues will be used as 
 techniques for oral practice. Grammatical structures will be introduced and 
 reviewed as needed.\n\nTopics 
 covered:\n\n\n	Music/songs/artists\n	Cooking/Food 
 description/Meals\n	Family\n	Daily routine with reflexive verbs/ 
 accessories\n	Past tense (preterite) of regular verbs and some irregular 
 verbs\n	Health and Well Being/Parts of 
 Body\n	Professions/Workplace\n	Clothing/Shopping\n\n\n\n\n \n
LOCATION:Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Language
