SUMMARY:The Corner Book Club Meeting
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a lively\, librarian-led discussion of "Alfred & 
 Emily"\, a revealing and intimate book by Doris Lessing.  \n\nIn this 
 moving book\, Nobel Laureate Doris Lessing explores the lives of her 
 parents\, each damaged by the Great War. In the fictional first half of 
 Alfred and Emily\, she imagines the happier lives her parents might have 
 made for themselves had there been no war. This is followed by an  
 examination of their relationship as it actually was in the shadow of the 
 devastating global conflict.\n\n
LOCATION:Montclair Bellevue Ave Branch - Classroom
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Bellevue Avenue Branch":MAILTO:branch-events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Bellevue Avenue Branch, Book Discussion
