SUMMARY:Lunar New Year Dessert Mochi Workshop NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nChinese dessert mochi\, or tang yuan\, are historically served 
 during the Lantern Festival\, the 15th day of the Lunar New Year. This 
 classic sweet has ventured far from its origins\, following the Chinese 
 diaspora as it traveled the world. Join us on this edible journey as we 
 make our own tang yuan. We'll begin traditional flavors such black sesame 
 peanut and then segue into the tastes of the new world with ube\, pumpkin\, 
 and more. Opening with a brief history of the tang yuan\, the program will 
 conclude with a tasting of our fresh creations.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Cafe Area\, Montclair Public Library
