SUMMARY:(POSTPONED) Waste Not\, Want Not Collage Workshop
DESCRIPTION:NEW DATE TBA DUE TO WEATHER\n\nThis is a paid Adult School 
 class. Click here to register.\n\nJoin professional painter Anna Berlin to 
 learn about the varied artists of the 20th century who helped make collage 
 a fixed idea of modern art and experiment with their techniques in class. 
 We will begin each two-hour class by looking at images of artworks and 
 discussing them. There will be a collage assignment for each class that 
 responds to the works and artists we shared. These assignments will also be 
 possible to make with items you can find in your home – highlighting the 
 adaptability and accessibility of the collage medium. Artists we will 
 discuss include Miriam Schapiro\, Melissa Meyer\, Hannah Höch\, Howardena 
 Pindell\, Betye Saar\, Ellsworth Kelly\, and Anne Ryan.\n\nA materials fee 
 of $14 will be charged at time of registration.  Registration is required.
LOCATION:Montclair Bellevue Ave Branch - First Floor\, Montclair Bellevue Avenue Branch
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
