SUMMARY:MILL @ MPL: Senior Fridays
DESCRIPTION:A day of activities for Seniors - every Friday!\n\n \n\nJoin us 
 on Fridays for a day full of events for Seniors with the MILL @ MPL! All 
 events are free and open to the public. Registration is recommended unless 
 otherwise noted.\n\nFollow this link to register for MILL classes.\n\nFor 
 questions about MILL classes please call 973-744-3278.\n\nMILL @ MPL is 
 made possible through a partnership between the MILL\, Montclair Public 
 Library and Partners for Health.\n\nFebruary 27 MILL @ MPL Senior Fridays 
 Schedule of Events:\n\n10:30 a.m. - 11:15 a.m.: Chair Yoga 
 (Auditorium)\n11:30 a.m. - 12:30 p.m.: CareBuilders presents: Brain Health 
 (Auditorium)\n12:30 p.m. - 1:30 p.m.: Lunch provided by Toni's Kitchen 
 (Auditorium)\n1:00 p.m. - 2:30 p.m.: Senior Craft: Decorative Tote Bags 
 (Classroom)\n1:30 p.m. - 3:30 p.m.: Book and Manuscript Illustration with 
 Maggie Rothman (Auditorium)\n\nPhotographs may be taken during our programs 
 and events for promotional purposes such as social media and e-newsletters. 
 If you do not wish to have your photograph taken please let us know before 
 the event.\n\nTo stay informed\, sign up for one or all of our 
 eNewsletters\, click here.
